</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="135" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="19" pageNumber="135" type="mainText">
Distribution. - Members of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="F. Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1877" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pseudomyrmex" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferrugineus">P. ferrugineus</taxonomicName>
group are found from eastern (San Luis Potosi, Tamaulipas) and western (Sinaloa) Mexico south through Central America to northern Colombia (Fig. 67). Although no single species spans the entire range of the group, their collective distribution is virtually identical to that of the swollen-thom acacias (compare Fig. 67 with Janzen 1974:3).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
